parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Accusative Feminine Plural
str2: Of what sort. From the base of pou and hoios; individualizing interrogative what sort of, or which one.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell, (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.
Of Hebrew origin; Jesus, the name of our Lord and two other Israelites.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: Answer, bid, bring word, command. A primary verb; to speak or say.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: To murder, kill. From phoneus; to be a murderer.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: To commit adultery (of a man with a married woman, but also of a married man). From moichos; to commit adultery.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: To steal. A primary verb; to filch.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: To testify falsely, bear false witness. From pseudomartur; to be an untrue testifier, i.e. Offer falsehood in evidence.
